[2026-03-07T17:02:13Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UxZ39XxZ5MZTd2o55QZx9s","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Project Versioning Design\n     2â†’\n     3â†’**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4â†’**Status:** Design\n     5â†’\n     6â†’## Problem\n     7â†’\n     8â†’After a self-reflection cycle mutates a workflow or prompt file, there is no record of\n     9â†’how many times the project has been evolved. This makes it hard to correlate behavior\n    10â†’changes with specific evolution events.\n    11â†’\n    12â†’## Design\n    13â†’\n    14â†’### Version file\n    15â†’\n    16â†’A plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`. The file is created with value `1` on\n    17â†’`cloche init`. The daemon increments it whenever the evolution pipeline produces at\n    18â†’least one change.\n    19â†’\n    20â†’```\n    21â†’.cloche/version\n    22â†’```\n    23â†’\n    24â†’Content is a single decimal integer followed by a newline, e.g. `3\\n`.\n    25â†’\n    26â†’### Increment rule\n    27â†’\n    28â†’In `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`, after Stage 5 (Audit), check:\n    29â†’\n    30â†’```go\n    31â†’if len(result.Changes) > 0 {\n    32â†’    incrementProjectVersion(o.cfg.ProjectDir)\n    33â†’}\n    34â†’```\n    35â†’\n    36â†’`incrementProjectVersion` reads `.cloche/version`, parses the integer, increments it,\n    37â†’and writes it back atomically (write to a temp file, rename). If the file does not\n    38â†’exist, it writes `2` (treating the missing file as implicit version 1).\n    39â†’\n    40â†’### Read path\n    41â†’\n    42â†’`config.Load` gains a companion function:\n    43â†’\n    44â†’```go\n    45â†’func LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)\n    46â†’```\n    47â†’\n    48â†’Returns the integer from `.cloche/version`, defaulting to `1` if the file does not\n    49â†’exist.\n    50â†’\n    51â†’### Surface\n    52â†’\n    53â†’- The project detail page (see project-pages design) reads the version via\n    54â†’  `/api/projects/{name}/info` and displays it as `v3`.\n    55â†’- The evolution audit log entry already records `ChangesJSON`; the version is not\n    56â†’  duplicated there.\n    57â†’\n    58â†’### .gitignore\n    59â†’\n    60â†’`.cloche/version` is **not** gitignored â€” it should be committed alongside workflow\n    61â†’changes so the version is visible in git history.\n    62â†’\n    63â†’`cloche init` adds `.cloche/version` to the files it creates (with content `1\\n`) but\n    64â†’does not add it to `.gitignore`.\n    65â†’\n    66â†’## Changes required\n    67â†’\n    68â†’| File | Change |\n    69â†’|------|--------|\n    70â†’| `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` | Call `incrementProjectVersion` when `len(result.Changes) > 0` |\n    71â†’| `internal/config/config.go` | Add `LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)` and `incrementProjectVersion` (unexported helper used by evolution) |\n    72â†’| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Write `.cloche/version` with content `1\\n` on init |\n    73â†’| `internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Include version in `/api/projects/{name}/info` response |\n    74â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"835b617a-c8b0-498c-ac2f-49c8473e6d27","uuid":"98a5e804-dbb4-494a-afe1-eff507be3595","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md","content":"# Project Versioning Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nAfter a self-reflection cycle mutates a workflow or prompt file, there is no record of\nhow many times the project has been evolved. This makes it hard to correlate behavior\nchanges with specific evolution events.\n\n## Design\n\n### Version file\n\nA plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`. The file is created with value `1` on\n`cloche init`. The daemon increments it whenever the evolution pipeline produces at\nleast one change.\n\n```\n.cloche/version\n```\n\nContent is a single decimal integer followed by a newline, e.g. `3\\n`.\n\n### Increment rule\n\nIn `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`, after Stage 5 (Audit), check:\n\n```go\nif len(result.Changes) > 0 {\n    incrementProjectVersion(o.cfg.ProjectDir)\n}\n```\n\n`incrementProjectVersion` reads `.cloche/version`, parses the integer, increments it,\nand writes it back atomically (write to a temp file, rename). If the file does not\nexist, it writes `2` (treating the missing file as implicit version 1).\n\n### Read path\n\n`config.Load` gains a companion function:\n\n```go\nfunc LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)\n```\n\nReturns the integer from `.cloche/version`, defaulting to `1` if the file does not\nexist.\n\n### Surface\n\n- The project detail page (see project-pages design) reads the version via\n  `/api/projects/{name}/info` and displays it as `v3`.\n- The evolution audit log entry already records `ChangesJSON`; the version is not\n  duplicated there.\n\n### .gitignore\n\n`.cloche/version` is **not** gitignored â€” it should be committed alongside workflow\nchanges so the version is visible in git history.\n\n`cloche init` adds `.cloche/version` to the files it creates (with content `1\\n`) but\ndoes not add it to `.gitignore`.\n\n## Changes required\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` | Call `incrementProjectVersion` when `len(result.Changes) > 0` |\n| `internal/config/config.go` | Add `LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)` and `incrementProjectVersion` (unexported helper used by evolution) |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Write `.cloche/version` with content `1\\n` on init |\n| `internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Include version in `/api/projects/{name}/info` response |\n","numLines":74,"startLine":1,"totalLines":74}}}
